{
  "format_version": 3,
  "name": "personas-role",
  "description": "Role-augmented variant of the bundled `personas` manifold \u2014 same 100-persona corpora, but each node's centroid is pooled under that persona's chat-template role substitution at fit time. Where `personas` lives in standard assistant-baseline activation space (the model representing 'assistant talking about persona X'), `personas-role` lives in persona-baselined activation space (the model representing 'I am persona X, speaking'). The persona-intrinsic axes should surface more cleanly because the shared assistant baseline is removed from each centroid. Drawn from Anthropic's Assistant Axis paper (arXiv 2601.10387) and the PSM framing; same cluster structure as `personas`.",
